@startuml
title SideHustle Position Creation Sequence

actor Student as User
participant "Client App" as Client
participant "PositionController" as PositionController
participant "PositionService" as PositionService
participant "SideHustleService" as SideHustleService
database "LaunchPad Data Store" as DB
participant "ConnectHub Classifieds\n(consumer)" as ConnectHub

User -> Client: Click create position and submit form
Client -> PositionController: POST /launchpad/sidehustles/{sideHustleId}/positions\nAuthorization: Bearer <jwt>
note right of PositionController
	JWT is validated before controller handling.
end note
PositionController -> PositionService: createPosition(sideHustleId, request, callerId)

PositionService -> SideHustleService: findOrThrow(sideHustleId)
SideHustleService -> DB: read side_hustles row
DB --> SideHustleService: SideHustle entity
SideHustleService --> PositionService: SideHustle owner data
PositionService -> PositionService: validate caller owns SideHustle

PositionService -> DB: insert positions row with status = OPEN
PositionService -> DB: update side_hustles.has_open_positions = true
DB --> PositionService: persisted position + side_hustle updates

PositionService --> PositionController: PositionResponse
PositionController --> Client: 200 OK + created position JSON
Client --> User: Show creation success message

== Public extension used by ConnectHub ==
ConnectHub -> PositionController: GET /launchpad/positions/{positionId}/status (public)
PositionController -> PositionService: getPositionStatus(positionId)
PositionService -> DB: read positions.status
DB --> PositionService: OPEN | FILLED | CLOSED
PositionService --> PositionController: plain status string
PositionController --> ConnectHub: 200 OK (text)

@enduml